                       <span class="newsxdd">2011-Apr-15 09:50</span>
   
      <span class="newsxdd"><br /></span>
   

         
      
      
      

                                   <span class="newsxabstract">Kuala Lumpur, 15 April 2011 - The Qi4j community today announced Release 1.3 of the innovative Java framework, </span><span class="newsxabstract"><strong>Qi4j</strong></span><span class="newsxabstract">. This release is significant for several customers, moving to deploy Qi4j in business critical 24/7 systems. "We now feel that the core features of Qi4j are as stable as software systems ever get. Qi4j is now being deployed at a major investment bank in the risk pricing domain.", said Niclas Hedhman, co-inventor of Qi4j together with Rickard Öberg, who added "Qi4j has really proved itself in StreamFlow, and I am convinced that many of our paradigms will stand the test of time."</span>
         
